- Fixed a bug where Fleet's stored Recovery Lock password state could become desynchronized from the managed macOS device. Apple removes the Recovery Lock password from the device when the MDM profile is removed, but Fleet previously continued to show the old password as verified after re-enrollment. This also unsticks hosts whose initial SetRecoveryLock command was abandoned when the device re-authenticated before acknowledging it. On any MDM re-enrollment, Fleet now soft-deletes the stored password so the recovery lock cron enqueues a fresh one.
